<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Differs from its only congener known from the Caucasus, 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. jawlowskii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="jawlowskii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. jawlowskii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mainly by the opisthomere possessing a striated rather than smooth lateral process, and a strongly rather than slightly bent anterior process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
