<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This ubiquitous, largely anthropochoric species was first listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lohmander, H" journalOrPublisher="Zoologischer Anzeiger" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B63" refString="Lohmander, H, 1936. Ueber die Diplopoden des Kaukasusgebietes. Goeteborgs Kungliga Vetenskaps- och Vitterhets-Samhaelles Handlingar, Ser. 5B, 5(1): 1-196." title="Ueber die Diplopoden des Kaukasusgebietes. Goeteborgs Kungliga Vetenskaps- och Vitterhets-Samhaelles Handlingar, Ser. 5 B, 5 (1): 1 - 196." year="1936">Lohmander (1936)</bibRefCitation>
and then repeated by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.741.20042" author="Kokhia, MS" editor="Stoev, P" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="35 - 48" refId="B52" refString="Kokhia, MS, Golovatch, SI, 2018. A checklist of the millipedes of Georgia, Caucasus (Diplopoda). In: Stoev, P, Edgecombe, GD, Eds., Proceedings of the 17th International Congress of Myriapodology, Krabi, Thailand. ZooKeys 741: 35 - 48, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.741.20042" title="A checklist of the millipedes of Georgia, Caucasus (Diplopoda)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.741.20042" volume="741" volumeTitle="Proceedings of the 17 th International Congress of Myriapodology, Krabi, Thailand." year="2018">Kokhia and Golovatch (2018)</bibRefCitation>
from central Georgia, Caucasus, but without any exact locality. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rakhmanov, RR" journalOrPublisher="Nauka Publishers, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B72" refString="Rakhmanov, RR, 1972. [Millipedes of the Lenkoran zone of Azerbaijan]. In: Ghilarov MS (Ed.) Problems of Soil Zoology. Materials of the IV All-Union Conference, Baku 1972. Nauka Publishers, Moscow" title="[Millipedes of the Lenkoran zone of Azerbaijan]. In: Ghilarov MS (Ed.) Problems of Soil Zoology. Materials of the IV All-Union Conference, Baku 1972." year="1972">Rakhmanov (1972)</bibRefCitation>
recorded this species from near Lankaran (= Lenkoran) in Hyrcania, southeastern Azerbaijan.
</paragraph>
